### Description

I installed the latest JDTLS version (1.18.0) and setup lspconfig by default config (require('lspconfig')['jdtls'].setup {}). When I open a java file, JDTLS doesn't work and returns nil, like in the picture below: 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/88051085/211248521-82426aae-c6f8-4662-9159-76458bd41c28.png)


### Neovim version

NVIM v0.8.2
Build type: Release
LuaJIT 2.1.0-beta3

### Nvim-lspconfig version

_No response_

### Operating system and version

Linux 6.1.4-arch1-1

### Affected language servers

jdtls

### Steps to reproduce

1. Install JDTLS
2. Default setup lspconfig by: require('lspconfig')['jdtls'].setup {}

### Actual behavior

The screen show nil in the bottom shown in picture in description.

### Expected behavior

_No response_

### Minimal config

```Lua
require('lspconfig')['jdtls'].setup {}
```


### LSP log

Doesn't generate log file at all.
